Arcane Jinxer	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx													PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=1],[PREVARGTEQ:Caster_Level_Highest__Arcane,1]											DESC:You can sacrifice arcane spells or spell slots in order to make it harder to resist your jinxes.																	SOURCEPAGE:p.26	BENEFIT: When you attempt to jinx a creature, you can expend one of your prepared arcane spells or available arcane spell slots to give your target a penalty on its jinx save equal to the level of the expended spell or spell slot. This does not alter the effect of the jinx, only the saving throw to resist the jinx.
Area Jinx		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Widen Spell																											DEFINE:AreaJinxRange|0	DESC:You can jinx multiple creatures so long as they are near each other.							STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE		BONUS:VAR|AreaJinxRange|10		SOURCEPAGE:p.26	BENEFIT:When you use your jinx, you create an instantaneous invisible burst with a maximum radius of %1 feet anywhere within the normal range of your jinx, affecting multiple targets. Any creature within this burst, regardless of whether or not you can see it, must make a saving throw to resist your jinx. If you use your jinx again, all of your current jinxes immediately end.|AreaJinxRange
Bolster Jinx	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Great Fortitude,Iron Will,Lightning Reflexes																										DESC:Your ability to resist certain effects somehow makes it even harder for creatures you jinx to do the same.															SOURCEPAGE:p.26	BENEFIT:A jinxed target's penalty on Fortitude, Reflex, or Will saves increases by 2 if you have the Great Fortitude, Lightning Reflexes, or Iron Will feat, respectively. If you have more than one of these feats, the additional penalties apply to all of the corresponding saves.
Distant Jinx	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx																																						DESC:Your jinx can affect creatures from farther away than normal.								STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE		BONUS:VAR|HalflingJinxRange|30	SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:The range of your jinx increases by 30 feet. You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects stack.
Fascination Jinx	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx,Bardic Performance																																		DESC:If you jinx an already fascinated creature, it doesn't fully recover until the jinx ends.																		SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:If you jinx a creature under the effect of a bard's fascinate ability, it also takes a -10 penalty on initiative checks while affected by the jinx. A creature under the effect of your fascinate ability has a -2 penalty on its save against your jinx.
Jinx Alchemy	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx,Alchemist ~ Swift Alchemy																																	DESC:With your knowledge of alchemy, creatures you jinx cannot benefit from most sorts of alchemical compounds.															SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:A jinxed creature cannot benefit from the effects of potions, elixirs, or any other substance that he must ingest in order to activate. This includes alchemical substances such as antitoxin, but not extracts, mutagens, or other alchemist class abilities that only affect the alchemist. A jinxed creature still takes any penalties and detrimental effects from ingested compounds or poisons.
Jinxed Spell	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.Metamagic	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx	PREABILITY:2,CHECKMULT,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Metamagic																													DESC:You can make a creature that fails its spell save suffer your jinx as well.																				SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:Any creature that fails its saving throw against a jinxed spell also suffers the effects of your jinx. This feat has no effect on spells that do not allow a saving throw. If the spell affects an area or multiple creatures, you must select one creature to take the jinx, unless you have the Area Jinx feat; if you have the Area Jinx feat, choose a jinx burst area within the spell's area or among its targets and apply the jinx to those in the burst that failed their save. A jinxed spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell's actual level.
Malicious Eye	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx,WitchHex ~ Evil Eye																																		DESC:You can combine the effects of your evil eye and your jinx.																							SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:When a creature fails its save against your evil eye hex, add the effect of your jinx to the effect of the hex. The save penalties from the hex and jinx stack. Using your jinx on another creature does not end the hex or the jinx effect on the hexed target.
Sluggish Jinx	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx																																						DESC:Your jinx makes creatures slow and clumsy.																										SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:Your jinx's penalty on saving throws also applies to the target's initiative and attack rolls.
Versatile Jinxer	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Iron Will																															DESC:Your jinx's power comes from a different source than most halflings.									MULT:YES	CHOOSE:PCSTAT|INT|WIS	BONUS:VAR|HalflingJinxDC|%LIST-CHA	SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:The DC of your jinx is based on your %1 score.|%LIST
Worst Case Jinx	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Jinx.WizardBonus	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Jinx																												PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Arcana)=5					DESC:Your jinxes hinder beneficial spells.																										SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:Beneficial variable effects on a jinxed target (such as aid, cure spells, false life, the variable ability damage cured by lesser restoration, and so on) always result in the minimum possible amount for the effect.
